Xinhua News Summary at 2115 GMT , November 21
TEHRAN -- Iran on Saturday rejected any foreign interference in Iraq after the United States announced readiness to support Iran 's efforts to topple Iraqi President Saddam Hussein .
" Any foreign interference in Iraq is illegal , " the commander of the naval forces of Iran 's Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps ( IRGC ) , Ali Akbar Ahmadian , said here at a press conference .
